d, and I am sure that the numbers of divorces skyrocketed at the same time step-families were presented in media. \n\nI know some of you may be part of such a family, and that's ok, I am just recollecting a memory I had. \n\nBasically, I have this memory of....either a book? Either some cartoon we watched at school and the premise was something with step-family. I know the morale of the story was something along the lines of \"And at the end, our hero found a family. And ----- became his father.\" \n\nNow naturally I was just a confused child clinging onto literal words, but looking back I realized this is peak propaganda telling you \"hey, your family is not important, you can easily abandon them\".\n\nI said to my teacher \"No. That's not true. You can only have one father. That's how biology works. You can't have two dads?\" And she told me I misunderstood and explained me the morale of the story and ending with 'and that's why this character became his father', but I still persisted saying that's not how biology works, he can be his STEP-father maybe, but not his father, cause you only have one father.\n\nThe teacher wasn't malicious or evil, I know she had this attitude where it was like \"oh yeh, he's a child, he'll get it when he grows up\" in a nutshell, but looking back at some of the things it's easy to understand the propaganda in books/cartoons/shows. \n\n", "author": "hisnamewasjeffTwo", "created": 1782219600068, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Mungo", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Who else had the 'right wing attitude' since young?", "last_comment_created": 1782225026088, "content": "<p>This is a lame title perhaps, but I just remembered a moment I had as a child and looking back, I realize that this was peak propaganda, the same one that's used for homosexuality these days</p>\n<p>Basically, before homosexuality was normalized, there was an anti-family propaganda.</p>\n<p>Of course, it was waaay less subtle than the current homo propaganda, but it existed and even as a kid it rubbed me off the wrong way, without knowing why.</p>\n<p>There were sooo many cartoons and shows where the message was &quot;your family is not family. real family is what you choose&quot;</p>\n<p>Like, there'd be some character in a book or something where the main character's dad would be presented as an alcoholic or something and he runs away from home and finds misfits, and now THEY are his family.</p>\n<p>And there was always this step-family thing being pushed, and I am sure that the numbers of divorces skyrocketed at the same time step-families were presented in media.</p>\n<p>I know some of you may be part of such a family, and that's ok, I am just recollecting a memory I had.</p>\n<p>Basically, I have this memory of....either a book? Either some cartoon we watched at school and the premise was something with step-family. I know the morale of the story was something along the lines of &quot;And at the end, our hero found a family. And ----- became his father.&quot;</p>\n<p>Now naturally I was just a confused child clinging onto literal words, but looking back I realized this is peak propaganda telling you &quot;hey, your family is not important, you can easily abandon them&quot;.</p>\n<p>I said to my teacher &quot;No. That's not true. You can only have one father. That's how biology works. You can't have two dads?&quot; And she told me I misunderstood and explained me the morale of the story and ending with 'and that's why this character became his father', but I still persisted saying that's not how biology works, he can be his STEP-father maybe, but not his father, cause you only have one father.</p>\n<p>The teacher wasn't malicious or evil, I know she had this attitude where it was like &quot;oh yeh, he's a child, he'll get it when he grows up&quot; in a nutshell, but looking back at some of the things it's easy to understand the propaganda in books/cartoons/shows.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 7, "score_up": 19, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2068946227941499258", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASt1HIxPV", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 311, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8693469, "raw_content": "", "author": "TRUTH_BE_OUR_DOGMA", "created": 1782164644898, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "AbelsRevenge", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASt1HIxPV.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/TruthFairy131/status/2068946227941499258", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "LB: In LONDON, an African attacks a WHITE man & the Police grab & arrest the WHITE guy. \r\n\r\nThen an overweight officer sits on his legs.\r\n\r\nTraitors protect foreign invaders. (VIDEO)", "last_comment_created": 1782211163642, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 19, "score_up": 311, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 2709, "created": 17